MicroMega, Pick n Pay and Sea Kay Might Move: South African Stocks Preview

-- B y   S i k o n a t h i   M a n t s h a n t s h a
-- 
2011-03-31T22:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-31/micromega-pick-n-pay-and-sea-kay-might-move-south-african-stocks-preview.html
The following stocks may rise or
fall in  South Africa . Symbols are in parentheses and prices are
from the last close.  South Africa’s FTSE/JSE Africa All Share Index fell 70.55,
or 0.2 percent, to close at 32,204.06 in Johannesburg.  1Time Holdings Ltd. (1TM)  (1TM SJ): The low-cost airline and
technical maintenance company said Michael Snyman has resigned
as finance director and will be leaving at the end of May. 1Time
declined 1 cent, or 1.5 percent, to 68 cents.  Micromega Holdings Ltd. (MMG)  : The  investment company 
with interests ranging from lubrication equipment to financial
services said earnings after one-time items declined to 15.9
million rand ($2.3 million) for the year ended December,
compared to 20.1 million rand a year earlier. The shares were
unchanged at 1.20 rand.  Pick n Pay Stores Ltd. (PIK)   was downgraded to “hold”
from “buy” at Cadiz Securities by equity analyst Shamil Ismail. The 12-month price estimate is 48 rand a share. Pick n
Pay fell 2.28 rand, or 4.7 percent, to 46.02 rand.  Sea Kay Holdings Ltd. (SKY)  : The builder of low-cost
houses narrowed its loss to 8.7 million rand in the first half
ended December, compared to a loss of 57.4 million a year
earlier, it said in an earnings statement filed with the stock
exchange. The shares increased 23 percent to 16 cents.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sikonathi Mantshantsha in Johannesburg at 
